cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS 

This paper focuses on backdoor attacks in the context of federated learning, which involves machine learning models trained on data distributed across multiple devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also discusses adversarial attacks, which fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper uses computer vision datasets (EMNIST) and discusses the performance of the attacks on different tasks, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the implementation of the attacks and defenses using TensorFlow Federated, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
